<doc>
  <member name="SCALE_CHANGE_FLAGS">
    <summary>
      <para>Flags that are used to indicate the scaling change that occurred.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="SCALE_CHANGE_FLAGS.SCF_VALUE_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>No change.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="SCALE_CHANGE_FLAGS.SCF_SCALE">
    <summary>
      <para>The scale factor has changed.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="SCALE_CHANGE_FLAGS.SCF_PHYSICAL">
    <summary>
      <para>The physical dpi of the device has changed. A change in the physical dpi is generally caused either by switching display devices or switching display resolutions.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>